00:05:18.980 --> 00:05:21.660
<v SPEAKER_2>It's very flattering to hear that.

00:05:22.940 --> 00:05:28.060
<v SPEAKER_2>Yet I don't really feel like personally like we're put on pedestal.

00:05:28.060 --> 00:05:30.940
<v SPEAKER_2>Of course, there's like noise and stuff.

00:05:30.940 --> 00:05:34.340
<v SPEAKER_2>But I think like people should take it with a grain of salt.

00:05:34.340 --> 00:05:41.160
<v SPEAKER_2>Because I mean, when we started this like, you know, five years ago, I mean, we were nobodies and we still are nobodies.

00:05:41.160 --> 00:05:42.100
<v SPEAKER_2>I mean, we're just normal people.

00:05:42.100 --> 00:05:58.420
<v SPEAKER_2>But it was hard to get in contact with people and people maybe took longer to reply to e-mails perhaps, or other companies, or other kind of, maybe people you looked up to, or I looked up to as like potential mentors, like, oh, like, hey, can you help me there?

00:05:58.420 --> 00:06:04.540
