00:06:27.540 --> 00:06:28.700
<v SPEAKER_2>You think you know all.

00:06:28.700 --> 00:06:37.980
<v SPEAKER_2>I mean, there's a huge survival bias in terms of sampling and like who speaks in these type of like settings and events.

00:06:37.980 --> 00:06:38.920
<v SPEAKER_2>So I'll be super careful.

00:06:38.920 --> 00:06:40.880
<v SPEAKER_2>And I guess it's not surprising.

00:06:41.100 --> 00:06:49.100
<v SPEAKER_2>I guess it's like, you know, with sports people, you know, if it's like a Michael Phelps or Usain Bolt, people want to dissect what they're doing.

00:06:49.100 --> 00:06:52.000
