00:08:16.180 --> 00:08:26.720
<v SPEAKER_2>Of course, you need to reflect and then be proud of yourself in terms of where you've come and compare yourself to the person you were like yesterday.

00:08:26.720 --> 00:08:35.760
<v SPEAKER_2>But at the same time, I am weary that there is a snowball effect and it's very easy to become detached and like ungrounded.

00:08:35.760 --> 00:08:38.860
<v SPEAKER_2>But of course, you have to enjoy successes and like small wins.

00:08:38.860 --> 00:08:39.440
<v SPEAKER_2>I'm not saying that.

00:08:39.440 --> 00:08:46.860
<v SPEAKER_2>I'm not saying like be like boring, but I think it's been a bit more like log on, I guess you would say.

00:08:46.940 --> 00:08:48.340
<v SPEAKER_1>Yes, sounds right.

00:08:48.340 --> 00:08:51.300
<v SPEAKER_1>In your head, do you think you actually...

00:08:51.300 --> 00:08:57.800
