00:11:16.820 --> 00:11:22.380
<v SPEAKER_1>Like it's, oh, fucking hell, it's like 60, 70, 80 people that I support from just this.

00:11:22.420 --> 00:11:22.660
<v SPEAKER_2>Yeah.

00:11:22.800 --> 00:11:31.900
<v SPEAKER_2>And I think like when we, during our time at Facebook, we were there during like the really turbulent political times in Cambridge, I think, and all that kind of stuff.

00:11:31.900 --> 00:11:49.660
<v SPEAKER_2>But one thing, you know, kind of maintained in the communications there, at least in the business group was that small businesses, like because I guess Facebook and those type of platforms really will help businesses like ours, like grow and acquire customers and like make customers happy with products and services.

00:11:49.660 --> 00:11:59.860
<v SPEAKER_2>But at the same time, essentially, they're supporting small businesses or businesses in general, because they create jobs, they create jobs and livelihoods for people.

00:11:59.860 --> 00:12:01.820
